beer_description: The beer that helped build our brewery; Bell?s Amber Ale features both toasted and sweet caramel notes from carefully selected malts, balanced with herbal and citrus hop aromas. Capped by a clean bitterness, it?s incredibly versatile with food, but very tasty on its own.

Hofbr?u M?nchen bietet mit ?M?nchner Sommer naturtr?b? eine nach traditioneller Rezeptur gebraute unterg?rige und naturtr?be Bier?gartenspezialit?t an, die so frisch und spritzig schmeckt, dass sie die ideale Alternative zum Wei?bier ist.

Im Glas entfaltet sich ?M?nchner Sommer naturtr?b? opal-schimmernd und m?rzenfarben mit einer feinporigen Schaumkrone. Das Bukett des unterg?rigen Bierklassikers mit rund 5,1% Vol. ist feinw?rzig und frucht?aromatisch. Sein Geschmack ist frisch, spritzig, estrig und mit einem subtil-herben Ausklang. Die Alternative zum Wei?bier!
A flavorful amber lager with a rich amount of hops in finish. A little fuller with more malty character than our Hofbr?u Lager.

Hofbr?uhaus is a symbol of Munich?s hospitality and the Bavarian gift for creating a snug and cosy atmosphere. Beer-lovers from all over the world come here to enjoy its famous beers. More than any other, Hofbr?u Original embodies the special atmosphere of the beer-making capital of Munich, and exports it to the four corners of the globe. Its refreshing, bitter flavour and alcoholic content of around 5.1% volume have made it famous worldwide. A Munich beer with character.

High Gravity Hybrid. Size Does Matter! First brewed in 2006 (and again in 2011) to push the limits of our own skills and imagination, Colossus is dark amber in color and full-bodied with a perceptively sweet flavor profile accented by notes of apple, and a surprisingly tame alcohol presence on the palate in light of its staggering 21.92% abv. This astounding alcohol content (the highest ever brewed in the state of Maryland and verified by the Siebel Institute) is achieved through fermentation alone; no alcohol is introduced at packaging nor it distilled. Multiple grains are used in conjunction with three different yeast strains to produce a beer that simply defies classification? and most laws of nature. One sip of this behemoth brew and you?ll agree: Sometimes size does matter!

This deep copper ale is unfiltered, full flavored and robust. An extended boil generated intense caramel notes, offset by an assertive hop bitterness. Raisin and dried cherry notes blend with shades of mild tropical fruit lead to a biscuit-like, slightly bitter finish.

Coolship Resurgam is a blend of both old and young unfruited spontaneous beer. The name comes from the motto of our fair city, Portland, Me. It means "I shall rise again". Coolship Resurgam won a Silver medal at the 2010 GABF.

Deep red-black in color, with a dense chocolatey brown head. Hogsback is mildly carbonated and aged longer than other ales. This English style stout is richer, smoother and slightly sweeter than typical Irish style stouts, making it popular among a wider range of beer aficionados. Extremely complex in its flavor and aroma it will at once give you impressions of coffee, chocolate, molasses, hops, sweet malt, and silky-smooth alcohol. A big beer to brew, but worth the extra effort! This is Mt. Hood's second-most popular beer. O.G. 1.064/ 4.5 abv/ Magnum, Mt. Hood, Cascade, Willamette hops/ Four different malts and rolled oats/ Molasses and licorice.
A wonderfully unique beer made with cherry wood smoked malts, Belgian yeast, rare sugar and 100% aged in whiskey and/or bourbon barrels. Suitable for aging.
Belgian-style Dubbel, created by Kevin McNerney.

Named after Fremont?s most famous outdoor sculpture, Waiting for the Interurban, Interurban India Pale Ale offers the adventurous beer lover a warm embrace of roasted pale malt swirled with a hand-selected blend of flavor malts and filled with the rich spice of Chinook, Centennial and Amarillo hops. Interurban India Pale is a session beer, eminently drinkable throughout the year.

beer_description:
Bonfire Imperial Porter has dark caramel, coffee, and chocolate notes and finishes
slightly sweet. Hop flavors add background spices and balance the full malt flavors.
Bonfire will please lovers of big, robust dark beers.

4.7% abv Dunkel lager. This superb sparkling ruby brown lager with its rich latte foam head is brewed with a blend of four malts, including crystal and cara malt, to create a burnt toffee multi-layered sweetness with a gentle bitterness.
Food Matches: Serve cool, great with a nutty Waldorf salad. Also good with cold roast meats, rustic pasta or Bangers and Mash. For dessert try a pecan toffee pastry.

Our Chocolate Porter pours a ruby black pint, topped with a creamy cocoa-brown head. Notes of caramel and roast blend with chocolate undertones from cocoa added to the conditioning tank. Finishes with a balanced dryness in the London style.

Lovingly referred to by Fremonters as the B-BOMB, this bourbon barrel-aged edition of our winter ale has a warming spicy aroma and rich carmelly notes of bourbon, wood and vanilla added to dark roasty chocolatey malt flavors and subtle hopping.

beer_description: Brewed with loads of malt and Belgian yeast, Pere Jacques is a wonderfully fruity, malty ale. Pere Jacques? complex flavors stand shoulder to shoulder with the Belgian Dubbels enjoyed in the world?s finest beer bars. At the dining table it?s the perfect alternative to a glass of vintage port.

Pineapple Pilsner is a refreshing American Pilsner with an exotic twist. Subtle esters of grain with hints of sweet citrus fruit collide with a mouth puckering snappy pineapple flavor that strikes the palate. A slight essence of malt and corn lead toward a relatively clean mouthfeel and a lingering tartness in the finish.

The Triple is a strong, full-bodied Belgian abbey-style ale. The authentic Belgian yeast strain used in fermentation contributes to a rich array of spicy, phenolic, and fruit-like flavors and noticeable alcoholic warmth. This unfiltered ale has an irresistible pale orange-colored hazy glow.
NON-BARREL AGED VERSION - Mephistopheles with coffee.
A truly full-bodied beer-rich, dark, malty and very complex. Belgian Abbey yeast, dark candi sugar and a huge assortment of specialty malts provide layers of complex aromas and flavors.
Displays a garnet copper color with flavors of caramel, toffee and a residual, yet distinct malty sweetness balancing a fair hop character.
Wheat ale brewed with honey, ginger, orange peel, and cherries. Happy Holiday's 6% ABV

A generous amount of hops produces the strong hop finish and dry hopping results in the mild, floral hop aroma. The luscious amber color belies a mellow palate and body. The mild character coupled with light conditioning results in a full tasting beer that can be enjoyed copiously.
Smooth as silk, full of flavor with a big malt and hop finish. Brewed with oatmeal, roasted barley, pale, caramel and chocolate malts and premium Chinook hops.
Single Malt And Single Hop
A "kitchen-sink" American Strong Ale brewed with 30 ingredients and aged on American Oak spirals. Draft-only limited release.
Made with raw wheat, coriander, Tellicherry and Indonesian long peppercorns.

A strong ale brewed with a blend of honey, red prickly pear juice, and a variety of pale malts. The addition of Alchemy hops helps balance the sweetness, while still retaining the natural honey aromas and flavors. Prickly pear juice adds a unique hue to the beer, as well as a subtle and refreshing herbal quality to the finish.

This medium bodied, copper colored strong lager is in a class all by itself. it has a delicate malty palate up front, which is abruptly overshadowed by the dominating hop presence which is attributed to the 1.5#/bbl. of hops added for aroma and flavor. Available twice a year in October and April.

Brewed to celebrate our first Christmas in 1989; ?NBA? is a medium bodied American brown ale, with a light hop aroma, deep rich color and nutty finish.

A medium bodied copper color India Pale Ale with bold citrus aromas from the use of real blood oranges and notable American hops. A shock of tart tangy fruit flavors are complimented by similar hoppy attributes, leading into an appropriate and enjoyable bitterness.

Brewed with loads of malt and Belgian yeast, Pere Jacques is a wonderfully fruity, malty ale. Pere Jacques? complex flavors stand shoulder to shoulder with the Belgian Dubbels enjoyed in the world?s finest beer bars. At the dining table it?s the perfect alternative to a glass of vintage port.

A southern German style of wheat beer (weissbier) made with a ratio of 65:35 wheat/pale malt. Authentic Hefe yeast was used to produce the unique phenolic flavors of banana and some spiciness of clove, it can also be perceived as notes of apples. Subtle Noble Hop bitterness (Hallertau Mittelfr?h) adds to the crisp complexity of this incredibly drinkable Ale. The "Hefe" prefix means "with yeast", hence the beers unfiltered and cloudy appearance.

Nose/aromas: Sweet malt, hints of tropical fruit (banana) and citrus fruits (oranges), suggestions of hops, light minerality.
Flavour: Playful in the mouth, pleasant bubbles, lovely malty attack followed by a fruity and slightly bitter touch, again a hint of minerality, nice dry finish.
A medium-bodied amber ale with a brilliant copper color. Top-fermenting ale yeast and a high proportion of imported Munich Malt create a clean crisp beer with a toasty, fruity backbone.
English style tap

NARBrew's Cranmerry Christmas Brown Ale.  Tis the season for Cranmerry Cheer!  Spread this cheer with the intensity and abundance found in a flavorful pint of this holiday brown ale.  Find out more at NARBrew.com

Meaning "rye bread" in Danish, we took our inspiration for this beer from the Danes' staple dark, whole-grain rye bread. Brewed with three types of rye malt, this robust brown ale showcases the earthy, spicy character of the grain, complemented by bready, nutty barley malts and a hint of roast. Loosely based on the Scandinavian Christmas beer of "Julebryg" tradition, this beer is perfect for the colder weather of winter, although it will be available year-round (because who doesn't love a dark beer now and again, regardless of weather?) And don't worry about the name, we can't pronounce it either! But we do have a video of us and a lot of other trying our best at it.
Crafted in the Pacific Northwest style, this American-style Crystal Wheat is immensely drinkable and perfect to quench your thirst. Creamy and malty with a mild hop bitterness.

Wassail! (good health!) is the greeting that peasants in the Middle Ages would give to farmers as they traveled around during the holidays banging drums, signing, and wishing them good luck in the next Year's crops.  The farmers would greet the well wishers
Dry, but with a creamy touch of Thai Palm sugar and the Spicy tang of rye, all balanced by loads of the wackiest new hops we could lay our hands on. Yep, it?s an original. And that?s no sin.
Aged in oak wine barrels

beer_description: The Duck-Rabbit M?rzen is the lightest of our German-style lagers. This is a beer designed for outdoor autumn festivals! Soft malt flavors take center stage here. This one is subtle and beguiling. ABV: 4.6%
A blend of barrel aged Rye Porter, Warmer Winter, and Big Sound.
A rich, well balanced foreign-style stout with a generous amount of roasted barley as well as chocolate, black, and caramel malts. Complex hop sequencing creates superbly balanced flavor.

Franziskaner Hefe-Weissbier Naturtr?b ist ein nat?rlicher und eleganter Weissbierprotagonist aus Bayern mit einem ?ppig wei?en Schaum. Das kupfergoldene Weizenbier mit hefetr?ber Opaleszenz entfaltet einen aromatischen Duft mit harmonischer Frucht in dem Bananen und Zitrusfr?chte gr??en lassen.

Durch den h?heren Kohlens?uregehalt ist es besonders spritzig und perlend. Seinen unverwechselbaren besonders frischen, dezent w?rzigen und fruchtigen Geschmack mit mild-s??lichem Ausklang entfaltet Franziskaner Hefe-Weissbier Naturtr?b beim genussvollen Herunterschlucken.

A throwback, historical ale brewed when English IPAs were hopped up to last the long voyage from England to Colonial troops in India, using English malts, English hops, and English yeast, and aged slightly on toasted oak for a 19th-century taste.

The winter solstice is the shortest day of the year.  Starting the following day the sun shines a little bit longer every day until the summer solstice.  This is known as the rebirth of the 'invincible sun' (sol Invictus).  At 9% ABV, this Belgian Dark Strong Ale will surely keep you warm as you await the return of summer.  Find out more about this and other NARBrew beers at http://NARBrew.com

beer_description: The recipe for our Easter Beer is based on a series of experiments trying to recreate an ale from a recipe on some old clay tables found in what is now called Iraq. The recipe, called "The Hymn to Ninkasi", describes in detail how beer was made using a mis of barley, honey, grapes and dates. Amber colored, slightly hazy beer with a white head. Soft sweet, slightly vineous aroma with hints of honey and hay. The body is light and the palate is complex with nutty, bready malts and hints of bisquit and bright citrus. Short, dry, slightly tart finish and only slight bitterness.
A beautiful copper-coloured ale, rich in caramel malt character and well balanced with plenty of hops. An authentic India Pale Ale, this IPA is handcrafted for the true ale drinker.
